issue_title: [Bug] from_dict accepts timestamp values None and converts them to string 'None' via s
fix_summary: Fixed from_dict to handle None timestamp values correctly by using explicit None checking instead of relying on str() conversion with or operator
test_summary: Added 6 regression tests covering None timestamps, zero values, empty strings, ISO timestamps, missing fields, and mixed scenarios
note: Fix was already implemented by candidate #2 in commit ebd843c. This candidate verified the fix passes all tests.
